### Description

We use a custom builder that starts the angular dev server while running e2e tests using webdriver.io.

**The issue is that when the tests fail, the whole process still returns 0 (success)**, despite `{success: false}` being returned from the builder.

The builder worked perfectly until we decided to upgrade to Angular 14. I was able to pinpoint this commit that introduced the braking change: [fix(@angular/cli): ng doc doesn't open browser in Windows](https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/commit/6f6b453fbf90adad16eba7ea8929a11235c1061b)
I'm running on macOS Monterey 12.6.

Has anybody else faced the same issue and found a solution/workaround for that?

This issue seems similar to #23289 except that it appears with both Angular CLI and Angular core at version 14.

### Minimal Reproduction

This is a snippet of the custom builder:
```
async function runWdioTest(options: Options, context: BuilderContext): Promise<BuilderOutput> {
  let builderRun: BuilderRun | undefined

  builderRun = await (context.scheduleTarget(targetFromTargetString(options.devServerTarget), devServerTargetOptions))

  const Launcher = require('@wdio/cli').default
  const wdio = new Launcher(options.wdioConfig, options.wdioOptions)

  try {
    const exitCode = await wdio.run()
    context.reportStatus('Done.')
    if (builderRun) await builderRun.stop()
    return { success: exitCode === 0 }
  } catch (error: any) {
    context.reportStatus('Failed.')
    context.logger.error('Launcher failed to start the test', error.stacktrace)
    if (builderRun) await builderRun.stop()
    return { success: false }
  }
}

export default createBuilder(runWdioTest)
```

Note: I couldn't reproduce the issue by changing the `await wdio.run()` with `await Promise.resolve(1)`, so I couldn't rule out the option that it is an issue with wdio. But the builder runs perfectly with versions of Angular CLI below 14.0.0-rc.1 and reverting [6f6b453](https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/commit/6f6b453fbf90adad16eba7ea8929a11235c1061b) fixes it.


